  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThis issue is to track support for listening for IPv6 connections on the HTTP API of the:\r\n- Beacon Node\r\n- Beacon Node metrics server\r\n- Validator Client\r\n- Validator Client metrics server\r\n\r\nOur web server framework `warp` supports listening for IPv6 connections (it also technically supports listening to both IPv4 and IPv6 at the same time), so supporting this in Lighthouse should just be a matter of allowing IPv6 addresses to be parsed by our CLI.\r\n\r\nCurrently we only accept `http-address`/`metrics-address` values [that are IPv4 values.](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/stable/beacon_node/src/config.rs#L96-L97)\r\n\r\nIt is trivial to enable parsing IPv6 values in the CLI by setting these fields to be `std::net::IpAddr` instead of `std::net::Ipv4Addr`\r\n\r\nThe tricky part will be ensuring the [CORS Origin for IPv6 addresses can be properly parsed](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/stable/common/warp_utils/src/cors.rs#L38-L55)\r\n\r\nSome initial testing indicates that `headers::Origin::try_from_parts` works for addresses formatted like `http://[::1]:5052` but not for addresses formatted like `http://::1:5052`.\r\n\r\nWe verify the CORS Origin through the [`set_builder_origin` function](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/stable/beacon_node/http_api/src/lib.rs#L257) which currently would format IPv6 addresses like `http://::1:5052`. \r\nSo the function here will need to be reworked. Since `IpAddr` is a `Enum` with `V4` and `V6` variants it should be possible to match on the variant and format them accordingly. \r\n\r\n\r\n",
